    "body": "> Is “the username and password is incorrect” a valid response to the question, “what if i do this thing?”\r\n> \r\n> My personal opinion is that it is a valid answer. It seems more correct than the cmdlet responding with “I’ll do this thing” when the thing is impossible for various reasons.\r\n\r\nI do agree with you in this regard, but I assume that you'd agree that the presented behavior ideally should be:\r\n1. a result of a **conscious decision**,\r\n1. **consistent** between:\r\n  a. handling files and directories by the same cmdlet (`New-Item -ItemType Directory` vs. `New-Item -ItemType File`),\r\n  b. handling directories by similar cmdlets (`New-Item` vs. `Copy-Item`)\r\n\r\n",
